.SH "NAME"
ccw_device_halt \- halt I/O request processing
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ ccw_device_halt('u
.BI "int ccw_device_halt(struct\ ccw_device\ *\ " "cdev" ", unsigned\ long\ " "intparm" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIcdev\fR
.RS 4
target ccw device
.RE
.PP
\fIintparm\fR
.RS 4
interruption parameter; value is only used if no I/O is outstanding, otherwise the intparm associated with the I/O request is returned
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
\fBccw_device_halt\fR
calls hsch on
\fIcdev\fR\*(Aqs subchannel\&.
.SH "RETURN"
.PP
\fB0\fR
on success, \-\fBENODEV\fR
on device not operational, \-\fBEINVAL\fR
on invalid device state, \-\fBEBUSY\fR
on device busy or interrupt pending\&.
.SH "CONTEXT"
.PP
Interrupts disabled, ccw device lock held
